<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">The point isn't that Enraged/Ireblind can or cannot be handled.  We all know it can.  I'm even touched by enough arrogance to believe my guild can take them down.  The point is that it's a zone with a level limit of 46 which is largely comprised of mobs designed in the original game.  It has drops that most of us wouldn't even consider good enough to carry back for tribute, the stuff isn't even as good as drops in zones of similar level that were designed AFTER the original game.  BUT it has drops that are necessary for some quests that have a high incentive rate to attempt: epics.  Further, the drops for some of those epics are so rare as to require many trips back to the zone.
<br />

<br />
Now, we have a zone that certain classes are highly incented to go to, with one single mob designed such that I'm certain no raid of 12 groups of 46th level characters can take down... not AND in that zone.  Give me the mob, or give me the zone, and the raid of 46s can do it, but, put both of them together, and I don't think it's possible.
<br />

<br />
Thus, we end up with a zone that requires a much higher level, much better prepared to boot, raid force to go and get.... sub par gear.  I know I'm exaggerating but it's a bit like forcing a time geared guild to go raid Fear... the ONLY thing in that zone that causes this problem is the Ireblind Imp.
<br />

<br />
The problem is:
<br />

<br />
1) Assume they make the Ireblind Imp non-Aggro.  Now he's trivial to kill.
<br />
2) Assume they make the Enraged/Ireblind mezzable.  Now he's trivial.
<br />
3) Assume they move him away from all the other critters in zone.  Now he's trivial.
<br />

<br />
On the one hand, he really breaks the zone and makes the risk vs reward just not worth it, on the other hand, I don't see an easy way to fix the problem.  The enraged, oddly, it a step in the right direction, but, they need to make the spawn rate of the Enraged more rare.  I've heard of groups facing three Enraged/Ireblinds in a night... and as pointed out, given that some of the drops are on mobs that only wpawn once a week, and are rare drops on top of that, this is going a bit far.  Personally, I think the Ireblind needs to be about as rare as the Golemns random 7 day timer or sume such.
<br />

<br />
I LIKE a challenge, I don't like beating my head against a brick wall just to see if I can draw blood.  I KNOW the blood is in there and don't really care for the headache.  The combination of Fear with the Ireblind IS a brick wall unless you go in espressly loking to take down the Ireblind.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
